---
import SubpageLayout from '@layouts/SubpageLayout.astro';

const _body = "<section class=\"sol-hero\">\n  <div class=\"container\">\n    <div class=\"section-label\" style=\"margin-bottom:1rem\">Solutions / E-commerce</div>\n    <h1>Pricing, Eligibility, and Promotions Without Drift</h1>\n    <p class=\"sol-hero-lead\">\n      E-commerce teams maintain the same pricing and promotion rules across web, mobile, and backend. Without a shared runtime, they drift. Traverse writes the rule once and runs it everywhere.\n    </p>\n    <div class=\"sol-hero-actions\">\n      <a href=\"/docs/quickstart.html\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-lg\">Get started</a>\n      <a href=\"/solutions.html\" class=\"btn btn-ghost btn-lg\">All solutions →</a>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</section>\n\n<section class=\"drift-section\">\n  <div class=\"container\">\n    <div class=\"section-label\" style=\"margin-bottom:0.75rem\">The drift problem</div>\n    <h2 class=\"t-h2\" style=\"max-width:600px;line-height:1.2\">Same promo code. Different results.</h2>\n\n    <div class=\"drift-scenario\">\n      <h3>Promotion: SUMMER20 — 20% off orders over $50</h3>\n      <div class=\"drift-row\">\n        <div class=\"drift-cell\">\n          <div class=\"env\">storefront</div>\n          <div class=\"val right\">$48.00</div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"drift-cell\">\n          <div class=\"env\">cart API</div>\n          <div class=\"val wrong\">$60.00</div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"drift-cell\">\n          <div class=\"env\">mobile app</div>\n          <div class=\"val wrong\">$48.00 *</div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"drift-cell\">\n          <div class=\"env\">fulfillment</div>\n          <div class=\"val wrong\">$60.00</div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"drift-label\">\n        * Mobile applies the discount but does not check the $50 minimum. Cart API does not apply it at all. Fulfillment uses a six-month-old version of the rule. All four were supposed to be identical.\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"problems-grid\" style=\"margin-top:2rem\">\n      <div class=\"problem-card\">\n        <div class=\"problem-card-num\">01</div>\n        <h3>Separate implementations that drift</h3>\n        <p>Promotion rules are coded independently in the storefront, cart API, and fulfillment worker. Each gets bug fixes and updates on different schedules. They diverge.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"problem-card\">\n        <div class=\"problem-card-num\">02</div>\n        <h3>Inconsistency between platforms</h3>\n        <p>Mobile gets a discount the web does not. Or vice versa. Customers notice. Support tickets follow. The fix goes to one place and misses two others.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"problem-card\">\n        <div class=\"problem-card-num\">03</div>\n        <h3>A/B testing multiplies the problem</h3>\n        <p>Testing two pricing variants means maintaining both versions in multiple places. When the test ends, cleaning up all the copies is error-prone. Some versions persist in production.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"problem-card\">\n        <div class=\"problem-card-num\">04</div>\n        <h3>AI recommendations need eligibility</h3>\n        <p>The recommendations model needs to know what a customer is actually eligible for. That logic lives in the backend. The AI team cannot call it safely without going through a governed interface.</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</section>\n\n<section class=\"solution-section\">\n  <div class=\"container\">\n    <div class=\"section-label\" style=\"margin-bottom:0.75rem\">What Traverse gives you</div>\n    <h2>One rule. Every environment.</h2>\n    <p class=\"lead\">\n      Write the pricing or eligibility logic once as a Traverse capability. The same WASM binary runs in the browser, the cart API, the fulfillment worker, and the AI pipeline. The contract enforces correctness before execution. The trace proves it ran correctly after.\n    </p>\n\n    <div class=\"solution-items\">\n      <div class=\"sol-item\">\n        <div class=\"sol-item-icon\">01</div>\n        <div class=\"sol-item-body\">\n          <h3>Single pricing capability</h3>\n          <p>The browser computes the price for instant display. The API confirms it at checkout. The worker applies it at fulfillment. All three use the same WASM binary. Same result every time.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"sol-item\">\n        <div class=\"sol-item-icon\">02</div>\n        <div class=\"sol-item-body\">\n          <h3>Governed promotions</h3>\n          <p>Eligibility rules are contracts. Invalid promo codes fail at the contract level before your database is touched. The precondition says what must be true before the discount is applied.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"sol-item\">\n        <div class=\"sol-item-icon\">03</div>\n        <div class=\"sol-item-body\">\n          <h3>Portable WASM binary</h3>\n          <p>Deploy the same capability to the storefront, checkout flow, and fulfillment service. No reimplementation. No sync meetings to coordinate rule changes across teams.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"sol-item\">\n        <div class=\"sol-item-icon\">AI</div>\n        <div class=\"sol-item-body\">\n          <h3>AI integration via MCP</h3>\n          <p>Expose your eligibility and pricing capabilities to AI agents as MCP tools. Agents call governed capabilities, not raw APIs. The same contract enforcement applies to every AI call.</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"highlight-callout\" style=\"margin-top:2.5rem\">\n      <strong>The flow with Traverse:</strong> storefront, cart, fulfillment, and AI pipeline each load the same capability from the registry. When the promotion rule changes, one version increment updates all of them. No coordination required.\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"env-flow\" style=\"margin-top:1.5rem\">\n      <div class=\"env-node active\">promotions.check-eligibility@2.1.0</div>\n      <div class=\"env-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"env-node\">storefront <span class=\"env-badge\">browser</span></div>\n      <div class=\"env-arrow\">+</div>\n      <div class=\"env-node\">cart API <span class=\"env-badge\">edge</span></div>\n      <div class=\"env-arrow\">+</div>\n      <div class=\"env-node\">fulfillment <span class=\"env-badge\">cloud</span></div>\n      <div class=\"env-arrow\">+</div>\n      <div class=\"env-node\">rec agent <span class=\"env-badge\">ai-pipeline</span></div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</section>\n\n<section class=\"use-cases-section\">\n  <div class=\"container\">\n    <div class=\"section-label\" style=\"margin-bottom:0.75rem\">Use cases</div>\n    <h2 class=\"t-h2\" style=\"max-width:500px;line-height:1.2\">Where e-commerce teams use Traverse first</h2>\n    <div class=\"use-cases-grid\">\n      <div class=\"uc-card\">\n        <span class=\"uc-num\">01</span>\n        <h3>Price calculation engine</h3>\n        <p>Base price, tier discounts, volume pricing, and currency conversion in one governed capability. Browser shows it. Backend confirms it. Fulfillment applies it.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"uc-card\">\n        <span class=\"uc-num\">02</span>\n        <h3>Promotion eligibility checking</h3>\n        <p>Promo code validation, minimum order requirements, customer tier gates, region restrictions. Enforced by contract. Fails fast before touching your database.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"uc-card\">\n        <span class=\"uc-num\">03</span>\n        <h3>Cart validation</h3>\n        <p>Stock availability, quantity limits, bundle rules, restricted items by region. Run in the browser for instant feedback and again at checkout for confirmation.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"uc-card\">\n        <span class=\"uc-num\">04</span>\n        <h3>Product recommendations with eligibility gates</h3>\n        <p>AI recommendation agents call the same eligibility capability your backend uses. Agents only surface products the customer can actually buy at the price shown.</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</section>\n\n<div class=\"container\" style=\"padding:4.5rem 0\">\n\n  <div class=\"section-label\" style=\"margin-bottom:0.75rem\">Code example</div>\n  <h2 class=\"t-h2\" style=\"margin-bottom:0.75rem\">Promotion eligibility contract</h2>\n  <p class=\"content-p\">\n    Here is the full contract for a promotion eligibility capability. The runtime reads it before every execution. If any precondition is unmet, the capability does not run. If any postcondition is violated, the result is rejected.\n  </p>\n\n  <div class=\"code-block\" style=\"margin:2rem 0\">\n    <div class=\"code-header\">\n      <div class=\"code-dots\"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div>\n      <span class=\"code-filename\">capabilities/promotions/check-eligibility.toml</span>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"code-body\">\n<span class=\"tok-section\">[capability]</span>\n<span class=\"tok-key\">name</span>      = <span class=\"tok-str\">\"promotions.check-eligibility\"</span>\n<span class=\"tok-key\">version</span>   = <span class=\"tok-str\">\"2.1.0\"</span>\n<span class=\"tok-key\">placement</span> = [<span class=\"tok-str\">\"browser\"</span>, <span class=\"tok-str\">\"edge\"</span>, <span class=\"tok-str\">\"cloud\"</span>, <span class=\"tok-str\">\"ai-pipeline\"</span>]\n\n<span class=\"tok-section\">[preconditions]</span>\n<span class=\"tok-comment\"># All enforced before execution. Cannot be bypassed by callers.\n# Invalid inputs are rejected here — not inside the function.</span>\n<span class=\"tok-key\">customer_id</span>  = <span class=\"tok-str\">\"non-empty string, max 64 chars\"</span>\n<span class=\"tok-key\">promo_code</span>   = <span class=\"tok-str\">\"non-empty string, alphanumeric, max 32 chars\"</span>\n<span class=\"tok-key\">cart_total</span>   = <span class=\"tok-str\">\"float, >= 0.0, max 999999.99\"</span>\n<span class=\"tok-key\">currency</span>     = <span class=\"tok-str\">\"ISO 4217 code\"</span>\n<span class=\"tok-key\">region</span>       = <span class=\"tok-str\">\"ISO 3166-1 alpha-2\"</span>\n<span class=\"tok-key\">customer_tier</span> = <span class=\"tok-str\">\"one of: guest, standard, silver, gold, platinum\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"tok-section\">[postconditions]</span>\n<span class=\"tok-comment\"># Enforced after execution. Output shape is guaranteed to callers.</span>\n<span class=\"tok-key\">eligible</span>       = <span class=\"tok-str\">\"boolean\"</span>\n<span class=\"tok-key\">discount_type</span>  = <span class=\"tok-str\">\"one of: percentage, fixed, free_shipping when eligible\"</span>\n<span class=\"tok-key\">discount_value</span> = <span class=\"tok-str\">\"float, >= 0.0 when eligible\"</span>\n<span class=\"tok-key\">reason</span>         = <span class=\"tok-str\">\"non-empty string when !eligible\"</span>\n<span class=\"tok-key\">expires_at</span>     = <span class=\"tok-str\">\"RFC3339 timestamp when eligible\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"tok-section\">[constraints]</span>\n<span class=\"tok-key\">max_execution_ms</span> = <span class=\"tok-num\">30</span>\n<span class=\"tok-key\">memory_limit_mb</span>  = <span class=\"tok-num\">8</span>\n<span class=\"tok-comment\"># Tight limits. This runs in the browser on every cart interaction.</span>\n\n<span class=\"tok-section\">[trace]</span>\n<span class=\"tok-key\">emit</span>      = <span class=\"tok-bool\">true</span>\n<span class=\"tok-key\">retention</span> = <span class=\"tok-str\">\"30d\"</span>\n<span class=\"tok-comment\"># trace_id links browser call → API confirmation → fulfillment application</span>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <p class=\"content-p\">\n    The storefront loads this capability and calls it on every cart update. The cart API loads the same capability and calls it at checkout to confirm. The fulfillment worker calls it before applying the discount. All three get the same result from the same binary.\n  </p>\n\n  <div class=\"code-block\" style=\"margin:2rem 0\">\n    <div class=\"code-header\">\n      <div class=\"code-dots\"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div>\n      <span class=\"code-filename\">storefront/src/cart/promo.ts</span>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"code-body\">\n<span class=\"tok-key\">import</span> { TraverseRuntime } <span class=\"tok-key\">from</span> <span class=\"tok-str\">'@traverse-framework/runtime'</span>;\n\n<span class=\"tok-key\">const</span> runtime = <span class=\"tok-key\">await</span> TraverseRuntime.<span class=\"tok-fn\">init</span>({ registry: REGISTRY_URL });\n\n<span class=\"tok-key\">export async function</span> <span class=\"tok-fn\">applyPromoCode</span>(\n  cart: Cart,\n  promoCode: <span class=\"tok-key\">string</span>,\n  customer: Customer,\n): Promise&lt;PromoResult&gt; {\n  <span class=\"tok-comment\">// Same capability the cart API and fulfillment worker use.</span>\n  <span class=\"tok-key\">const</span> result = <span class=\"tok-key\">await</span> runtime.<span class=\"tok-fn\">execute</span>(\n    <span class=\"tok-str\">'promotions.check-eligibility@2.1.0'</span>,\n    {\n      customer_id: customer.id,\n      promo_code: promoCode,\n      cart_total: cart.subtotal,\n      currency: cart.currency,\n      region: customer.region,\n      customer_tier: customer.tier,\n    }\n  );\n\n  <span class=\"tok-comment\">// Postconditions guaranteed. No defensive null-checking needed.</span>\n  <span class=\"tok-key\">if</span> (!result.output.eligible) {\n    <span class=\"tok-key\">return</span> { applied: <span class=\"tok-bool\">false</span>, reason: result.output.reason };\n  }\n\n  <span class=\"tok-key\">return</span> {\n    applied: <span class=\"tok-bool\">true</span>,\n    discount_type: result.output.discount_type,\n    discount_value: result.output.discount_value,\n    expires_at: result.output.expires_at,\n    trace_id: result.trace_id, <span class=\"tok-comment\">// passed to API for confirmation</span>\n  };\n}\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"highlight-callout\">\n    <strong>The trace_id travels end to end:</strong> the browser call, the API confirmation, and the fulfillment application all carry the same trace_id. When a customer disputes a discount, you can pull the full execution chain in one query.\n  </div>\n\n  \n    </div>\n</section>\n\n<section class=\"cta-band\">\n  <div class=\"cta-band-glow\"></div>\n  <div class=\"container\" style=\"position:relative;z-index:1;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:2rem;flex-wrap:wrap\">\n    <div>\n      <div class=\"t-h3\" style=\"margin-bottom:0.5rem\">Fix your promotion drift.</div>\n      <div class=\"t-body t-muted\">One capability. Every environment. Contract-enforced from day one.  </div>\n</section>\n    <div style=\"display:flex;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap\">\n      <a href=\"/docs/quickstart.html\" class=\"btn btn-primary btn-lg\">Quickstart</a>\n      <a href=\"/solutions.html\" class=\"btn btn-ghost btn-lg\">All solutions →</a>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"display:flex;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-top:1rem\">\n    <a href=\"/solutions/enterprise.html\" class=\"btn btn-ghost\">Traverse for Enterprise →</a>\n    <a href=\"/compare/vs-function-calling.html\" class=\"btn btn-ghost\">Traverse vs AI Function Calling →</a>\n  </div>\n\n</div>";
---
<SubpageLayout
  title={"Traverse for E-commerce: Pricing, Eligibility, and Promotions Without Drift · Traverse Framework"}
  description={"E-commerce teams maintain pricing, promotion, and eligibility rules across web, mobile, and backend. Traverse writes it once and runs it everywhere."}
  canonical={"https://traverse-framework.com/solutions/ecommerce.html"}
  crumbs={[{ label: "Home", href: "/" }, { label: "Solutions", href: "/solutions.html" }]}
>
  <style is:global slot="head">.sol-hero::before {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      background: radial-gradient(ellipse 50% 55% at 15% 50%, var(--accent-dim) 0%, transparent 65%);
      pointer-events: none;
    }
    .sol-hero h1 {
      font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 4.5vw, 3.4rem);
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
      line-height: 1.1;
      margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      max-width: 720px;
    }
    .sol-hero-lead {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      color: var(--fg-muted);
      max-width: 580px;
      line-height: 1.75;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
    .sol-hero-actions { display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }

    .drift-section {
      padding: 4rem 0;
      background: var(--bg-elevated);
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .drift-scenario {
      background: var(--bg-card);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 2rem;
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
    }
    .drift-scenario h3 {
      font-size: 1rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      color: var(--fg);
      margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    }
    .drift-row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(180px, 1fr));
      gap: 1px;
      background: var(--border);
      border-radius: 8px;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .drift-cell {
      background: var(--bg-elevated);
      padding: 1rem;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .drift-cell .env {
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      color: var(--fg-muted);
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    .drift-cell .val {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      font-family: var(--font-display);
    }
    .drift-cell .val.wrong { color: var(--danger); }
    .drift-cell .val.right { color: var(--success); }
    .drift-label {
      font-size: 0.82rem;
      color: var(--fg-muted);
      margin-top: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .problems-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
      gap: 1.25rem;
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
    }
    .problem-card {
      background: var(--bg-card);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }
    .problem-card-num {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      color: var(--fg-muted);
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      background: var(--bg-elevated);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
      border-radius: 4px;
    }
    .problem-card h3 {
      font-size: 1rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
    }
    .problem-card p {
      font-size: 0.88rem;
      color: var(--fg-muted);
      line-height: 1.65;
    }

    .solution-section { padding: 4.5rem 0; }
    .solution-section h2 {
      font-size: 1.9rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    }
    .solution-section .lead {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      color: var(--fg-muted);
      max-width: 600px;
      line-height: 1.75;
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }
    .solution-items {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }
    .sol-item {
      display: flex;
      gap: 1rem;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }
    .sol-item-icon {
      width: 40px;
      height: 40px;
      background: var(--accent-dim);
      border: 1px solid var(--accent);
      border-radius: 8px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      font-size: 1rem;
      flex-shrink: 0;
      margin-top: 0.1rem;
    }
    .sol-item-body h3 {
      font-size: 0.98rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    }
    .sol-item-body p {
      font-size: 0.88rem;
      color: var(--fg-muted);
      line-height: 1.65;
    }

    .use-cases-section {
      padding: 4rem 0;
      background: var(--bg-elevated);
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .use-cases-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
      gap: 1.25rem;
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
    }
    .uc-card {
      background: var(--bg-card);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 1.5rem;
      transition: border-color 0.2s;
    }
    .uc-card:hover { border-color: var(--accent); }
    .uc-num {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      color: var(--accent);
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      display: block;
    }
    .uc-card h3 {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      color: var(--fg);
    }
    .uc-card p {
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      color: var(--fg-muted);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .highlight-callout {
      background: var(--bg-elevated);
      border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
      border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
      padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
      margin: 2rem 0;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: var(--fg-muted);
      line-height: 1.75;
      max-width: 720px;
    }
    .highlight-callout strong { color: var(--fg); }

    .content-p {
      color: var(--fg-muted);
      line-height: 1.8;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      max-width: 680px;
      font-size: 0.97rem;
    }

    .env-flow {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0;
      margin: 2rem 0;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }
    .env-node {
      background: var(--bg-card);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 0.6rem 1rem;
      font-size: 0.82rem;
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      color: var(--fg-muted);
      white-space: nowrap;
    }
    .env-node.active {
      border-color: var(--accent);
      color: var(--accent);
      background: var(--accent-dim);
    }
    .env-arrow {
      color: var(--border);
      font-size: 1rem;
      padding: 0 0.5rem;
    }
    .env-badge {
      background: var(--accent-dim);
      border: 1px solid var(--accent);
      color: var(--accent);
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
      border-radius: 4px;
      margin-left: 0.4rem;
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .solution-items { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .drift-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    }
    @media (max-width: 480px) {
      .drift-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .env-flow { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; }
    }</style>
  <Fragment set:html={_body} />
</SubpageLayout>
